df52db578d711579b9cc26c94d8b3d41 (12:01): aneurysm: you can
5b9a270c7febb8bfc21f7732c2b4fdee (12:02): munter: how?
df52db578d711579b9cc26c94d8b3d41 (12:02): just execute it where you want it instead of in an event handler
df52db578d711579b9cc26c94d8b3d41 (12:03): But if google tells you to use the onload event handler, there is probably a reason
df52db578d711579b9cc26c94d8b3d41 (12:03): Like, the page has to be done loading or the script breaks
df52db578d711579b9cc26c94d8b3d41 (12:03): Most script plugins like that require a valid DOM at the time of execution
df52db578d711579b9cc26c94d8b3d41 (12:03): I know mine do
